turn.2: South Lakeland South Lakeland is a local government district in Cumbria, England.
turn.4: The population of the non-metropolitan district at the 2011 Census was 103,658.
turn.6: Its council is based in Kendal.
turn.8: It includes much of the Lake District as well as northwestern parts of the Yorkshire Dales.
turn.10: The district was created on 1 April 1974 under the Local Government Act 1972.
turn.11: Is there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.12: It was formed from the Kendal borough, Windermere urban district, most of Lakes urban district, South Westmorland Rural District, from Westmorland, Grange and Ulverston urban districts and North Lonsdale Rural District from Lancashire, and Sedbergh Rural District from the West Riding of Yorkshire.
